US idiom for a breakfast consisting of "A cigarette and a glass of water" - supposedly because that is all some Mexicans can afford. The phrase, generally used in obviously derogatory metaphors and similies,is part of a theme in US slang where the adjective "Mexican" implies something substandard or pointless.

